sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client
    participant AGW as Agent Gateway
    participant Backend as Backend Service (TLS-only)

    Note over Client,Backend: Inbound: mTLS via FrontendTLS (TLSConfig with CA root)
    Client->>AGW: ClientHello
    AGW->>Client: ServerHello + Server Certificate<br/>+ CertificateRequest (trusted CA list)
    Client->>AGW: Client Certificate + CertificateVerify
    AGW->>AGW: Verify client cert against CA root

    alt Client cert valid
        Note over Client,AGW: mTLS session established
        Client->>AGW: Request (over mTLS channel)
    else Client cert invalid or missing
        AGW->>Client: TLS handshake failure<br/>(connection refused — no HTTP layer reached)
    end

    Note over AGW,Backend: Outbound: TLS Origination via BackendTLSPolicy
    AGW->>Backend: TLS ClientHello
    Backend->>AGW: Server Certificate
    AGW->>AGW: Verify backend cert against<br/>caCertificateRefs or wellKnownCACertificates
    AGW->>Backend: Forward request (new TLS connection)
    Backend-->>AGW: Response (encrypted)
    AGW-->>Client: Response

    Note over Client,Backend: FrontendTLS (TLSConfig.root):<br/>Validates inbound client certificates.<br/>BackendTLSPolicy (caCertificateRefs):<br/>Originates outbound TLS to backends.
